The paper deals with sequences of vectors and their properties, which are typically studied in the areas of data structures (cs.DS) and discrete mathematics (cs.DM). The use of resets and increments suggests a connection to coding theory and information theory (cs.IT), while the length of the sequence and the non-dominating property may involve computational complexity (cs.CC) and numerical analysis (cs.NA).
